&lt;p&gt;I need to support a URI which looks like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;/user/5/foo;a=1;b=2&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where "foo" is a literal string. Since MVC only allows matrix variables on path variables, the corresponding request mapping looks like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;/user/{userId}/{foo&lt;/tt&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since that would allow the foo variable to be anything, I restricted it using a regular expression, and the mapping became&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;/user/{userId}/{foo:foo&lt;/tt&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At which point, my matrix variables stopped working. I've attached a Gist showing how matrix variables don't work when the path variable has a regex restriction. In that Gist, &lt;tt&gt;/withoutRegex/3&lt;/tt&gt; works with both matrix variables and without matrix variables. &lt;tt&gt;/withRegex/3&lt;/tt&gt; works without matrix variables, but when I specify matrix variables, I get the error &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;No mapping found for HTTP request with URI &lt;span class="error"&gt;&amp;#91;/withRegex/3;q=10&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; in DispatcherServlet with name 'dispatcherServlet'&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;MBeanExporter#autodetect()&lt;/tt&gt; method is supposed to register all the beans in the JMX server.&lt;br/&gt;
It calls &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id="syntaxplugin" class="syntaxplugin" style="border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;"&gt;
