&lt;p&gt;Loading properties using &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;context:property-placeholder .. /&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;, i.e. from a set of files, allows these to be overridden by the surrounding environment, e.g. using system properties. Supposing the properties loaded by the &lt;tt&gt;PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt; contained two "default" properties &lt;tt&gt;p1=v1&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;p2=v2&lt;/tt&gt;, any of these could be overridden using a concrete value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if one tries to override &lt;p/&gt;
