&lt;p&gt;Messages sent from server to user queue(from methods with @SendToUser) will also be sent to clients that subscribed with glob pattern '/queue/*'&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Setup is: webmvc+(stomp over sockjs).&lt;br/&gt;
In attached tests:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;connect 2 stomp clients&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;subscribe client 1 to '/user/queue/*'&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;subscribe client 2 to '/queue/*'&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;send message from client 1 to 'echo' service ,that has @SendToUser('/queue/echo') annotation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;expect client 1 to get two messages(connect reply,echo message)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;expect client 2 to get one message (connect reply)&lt;br/&gt;
Fail: client 2 got two messages, second one with 'destination:/user/queue/echo'&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As mentioned in &lt;a href="http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/PropertyResourceConfigurer.html:" class="external-link" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/beans/factory/config/PropertyResourceConfigurer.html:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; the convertPropertyValue method has been documented as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="panel" style="border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="panelContent"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Convert the given property value from the properties source to the value which should be applied.&lt;br/&gt;
The default implementation simply returns the original value. Can be overridden in subclasses, for example to detect encrypted values and decrypt them accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

