&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Buffer sizes for outgoing websocket messaging were set to low values to speed up "send limit" failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally, I started to monitor the quantity (webSocketConfig is just the object I use to configure websockets, it has abovementioned getCustomtasExecutor() and configures Outbound Channel to use it. It simply stores the generated Executor for later use, so I can just use it like
&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id="syntaxplugin" class="syntaxplugin" style="border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;"&gt;
&lt;table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%" style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.4em !important; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: black;"&gt;
