&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;that appears also as "queued tasks" for outbound channel in Websocket standard logging.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;What happened:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Deliberately slow message processing has been introduced for Websocket.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A client was disconnected with status 1006.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Around this time (slightly earlier maybe) Queue starts to build up.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While more clients were still connected, Queue continued to grow.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When all clients were disconnected, Queue size remained big, albeit stabilized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Apart from blocking the sending, Queue in taskExecutor is not cleaned and leaking memory therefore. Slow clients that are disconnected with non-OK errors, such as send limit, will make this problem appear and memory/Queue leaked, resulting at some point in non-responsive application.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected behaviour&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Tasks related to disconnected websocket should be pulled from queue.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When all clients are disconnected, task queue should be empty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



