&lt;p&gt;What I observe:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JaxWsProxyFactoryBeanDefinitionParser is called to construct the &amp;lt;jaxws:client ../&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;BreakTransactionalFeature gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SpringTransactionConfiguration gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ProxyTransactionManagementConfiguration.transactionAdvisor()-bean gets constructed
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;All new beans now get the required @Transactional-proxy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TestController gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Observe that BreakTransactionalFeature on the TestController doesn't have a Proxy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;What I expected:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SpringTransactionConfiguration gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ProxyTransactionManagementConfiguration.transactionAdvisor() gets constructed
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;All new beans now get the required @Transactional-proxy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JaxWsProxyFactoryBeanDefinitionParser is called to construct the &amp;lt;jaxws:client ../&amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;BreakTransactionalFeature gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TestController gets constructed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Observe that BreakTransactionalFeature has a Proxy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There is however a workaround by changing the BreakTransactionalFeature from constructor Injection to Field-injection. (yay!) Switching from @EnableTransactionManagement to XML also fixes the problem weirdly enough. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my opinion all beans should get processed by the @Transactional or no beans get processed, so it is consistent.&lt;br/&gt;
Even If this is a CXF bug, spring should still throw an exception or log an error and not fail silently. Do you agree?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I included an example showcasing the bug, &lt;a href="https://github.com/ChristianHersevoort/spring-transactionmanager-bug" class="external-link" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://github.com/ChristianHersevoort/spring-transactionmanager-bug&lt;/a&gt; . Clone repo and run "mvn jetty:run"&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are using spring version 4.2.8 and tomcat 7. And we got deadlock when tomcat started closing websocket session and in the same time AbstractSockJsSession started hearbeat task.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="green"&gt;THREAD 1&lt;/font&gt;:&lt;br/&gt;
org.springframework.web.socket.sockjs.transport.session.AbstractSockJsSession.HeartbeatTask&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; &lt;font color="red"&gt;LOCK org.springframework.web.socket.sockjs.transport.session.AbstractSockJsSession#responseLock LOCK&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.springframework.web.socket.sockjs.transport.session.AbstractSockJsSession#sendHeartbeat&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.springframework.web.socket.sockjs.transport.session.AbstractSockJsSession#writeFrame&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.springframework.web.socket.sockjs.transport.session.WebSocketServerSockJsSession#disconnect&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.springframework.web.socket.adapter.AbstractWebSocketSession#close(org.springframework.web.socket.CloseStatus)&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.springframework.web.socket.adapter.standard.StandardWebSocketSession#closeInternal&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#close(javax.websocket.CloseReason)&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#doClose&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; &lt;font color="red"&gt;DEADLOCK org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#stateLock DEADLOCK&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="green"&gt;THREAD 2&lt;/font&gt;:&lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#onClose &lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; &lt;font color="red"&gt;LOCK org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#stateLock LOCK&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-&amp;gt; org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsSession#fireEndpointOnClose&lt;br/&gt;
