&lt;p&gt;There is a SqlMapClient.openSession(Connection) method and I think this is what should be used in SqlMapClientTemplate instead of openSession() (the connection should be springCon somehow or its equivalent). I am not sure if using openSession(connection) is ok in all cases, but seems to me like what it should be to avoid those extra connection/jndi lookups.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should use AccessController.doPrivileged in RuntimeTestWalker constructor.&lt;br/&gt;
This way, we would only have to add &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;permission java.lang.reflect.ReflectPermission "suppressAccessChecks";&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;for spring jars in policy file.&lt;/p&gt;

